body_html: If you want training to start sooner, you should reduce the value of min_after_dequeue. This parameter is here to ensure good mixing, so you may find that the loss of randomness leads to poorer accuracy, but this depends on your model.

body: If you want training to start sooner, you should reduce the value of `min_after_dequeue`. This parameter is here to ensure good mixing, so you may find that the loss of randomness leads to poorer accuracy, but this depends on your model.
